---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { siteData } from '../lib/data';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<BaseLayout title={`${siteData.brand} | Call for Speakers`}>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">Get involved</p>
      <h1>Call for speakers</h1>
      <p>
        The number one thing that user groups like ours need are <strong>speakers</strong>.
        Venues and sponsors and swag come and go — but human beings willing to share their
        technical knowledge is the number one commodity for a user group.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="button" href="https://sessionize.com/brug" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Submit on Sessionize</a>
        <a class="button-secondary" href={`mailto:${siteData.contactEmail}?subject=Speaking at BRSSUG`}>Email us</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="panel prose-panel">
    <h2>What does it take to speak?</h2>
    <p>
      Not expertise, not experience, and not a fancy impressive slide deck — though all those
      things are helpful. Got an interesting project at work? A master's or doctoral thesis
      to research presenting? Blogged about an interesting solution to a problem? Excited about
      a piece of software? <strong>We'd like to hear from you.</strong>
    </p>
    <p>
      Code demos are great tools and can be more informative and interesting than a PowerPoint
      alone. Bring whatever you've got.
    </p>

    <h2>How long do I have to speak?</h2>
    <p>
      You tell us — there's no set schedule. If you'd like only to kick off a meeting with a
      15-minute talk, we'll gladly schedule you for that. Anywhere from <strong>15 to 90 minutes</strong>
      is what we try to fill during a user group, and you're entitled to any portion of that.
    </p>

    <h2>What do I get out of it?</h2>
    <p>
      Whether speaking at a user group is the pinnacle of your technical speaking career, the
      beginning, or a stepping stone — our group is the perfect opportunity to increase your
      experience and confidence. You'll find only a positive environment of peers where you
      can grow as a speaker. No nonconstructive, cynical, or condescending remarks — ever.
    </p>

    <h2>Employer sponsorship</h2>
    <p>
      Many speakers get encouragement from their employers in the form of a user group sponsorship,
      where your sales and marketing folks can meet and greet attendees of both the .NET and SQL
      user groups. If you'd like to schedule a meeting where your employer can also attend as a
      sponsor, we can definitely do that. See our <a href={`${base}/sponsorship/`}>sponsorship page</a> for details.
    </p>

    <h2>Ready? Let's get you on the schedule.</h2>
    <p>
      Email us at <a href={`mailto:${siteData.contactEmail}`}>{siteData.contactEmail}</a> and
      we'll work out a date. You can also submit your talk directly through our
      <a href="https://sessionize.com/brug" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Sessionize Call for Speakers page</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
